cs.CY, cs.HC, cs.CR, cs.SI, cs.CL

This paper focuses on understanding children's perception of privacy risks online, which falls under the category of cybersecurity (cs.CY). The study also involves focus group studies with children, which relates to human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The paper discusses privacy risks and how children identify them, which could be categorized under computer crime and security (cs.CR) and social and information networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper also touches upon language and communication, as it examines how children articulate their understanding of privacy risks, which could fall under computational linguistics (cs.CL).
